title.narrative: The three packages of line transfers from BPDB to REB are implemented.

comment.narrative: 4,000 km lines transferred by credit effectiveness.
The target of the original credit was 9,400 km lines transferred in three packages. The target was revised to 12,000 km lines inthree packages under the first additional credit.
11,295 km lines transferred. The component has closed by now.

title.narrative: (i) Grid-Based system to serve about 700,000 additional rural households, small and medium enterprizes and public institutions.

comment.narrative: Due to moratorium on new connections, REB could not add new connections for some time, which caused the lower number ofconnectionscompared to the target. The REB components have closed by by now.

title.narrative: People provided with access to electricity by household connections

comment.narrative: The targets have already been met due to higher number of off-grid connections supported under the project.
This is both from grid and off-grid connections supported under the project.

title.narrative: People provided with access to electricity by hhold connections-Grid

comment.narrative: The grid connection target was 700,000. Due to moratorium on new connections, the achievement is slightly lower than the targets.
This is calculated from the number of grid connections supported under the project multiplied by the average household size of 4.5.

title.narrative: Generation Capacity of Renewable Energy constructed-Solar

comment.narrative: The average size of the solar home systems supported under the project was assumed to be 50Wp.
This is the total capacity of the solar home systems supported under the project as of October 31, 2012.

title.narrative: Generation Capacity of Renewable Energy (other than hydropower) constructed
More efficient energy consumption through installiation of compact fluorescent lamps

comment.narrative: The target will not be met. The second phase of 17.5 million CFLs will not be completed under the project. Allocation for thesecond phase is being canceled and fresh allocations have been made in the recently approved new project (RERED II).
There have been quality issues in the bulbs distributed.

title.narrative: Expanded access to electricity in rural areas through other renewable energy options

comment.narrative: No more mini-grids will be supported under the project. .
These are renewable energy based mini grids (one is based on solar PV, and the other two are biomass gasification plants).

title.narrative: Ppl provided wth elec. by hhold conn.–Offgrid/minigrid–Only renewable sources

comment.narrative: The project started with 64,000 SHS target under the original credit. The first additional financing target was an additional300,000 SHS and the second additional financing target was another 630,000 systems.
This is from the solar home systems supported under the project as of October 2012.

title.narrative: Expanded access to electriicity in rural areas through solar home systems

comment.narrative: This is the total target of IDCOL that will be funded by IDA and other donors. The target for IDA support is 994,000. The secondadditional financing has a target of 630,000 systems by project closing.

This is the total number installed by IDCOL with support from IDA and other development partners. IDA supported a total of1,061,869 systems that includes 483,997 systems under second additional financing (as of October 2012). The second additionalfinancing target of 630,000 is likely to be exceeded by the project closing in December 2012.

title.narrative: Providing rural access by solar home systems

comment.narrative: This is the target for capital buy-down grant support.
This is the total number of SHS supported through capital buy-down grant from the GEF component.
